proguard.evaluation

Class Processor

  • java.lang.Object
    • proguard.evaluation.Processor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InstructionVisitor

    public class Processor
extends java.lang.Object
implements InstructionVisitor
    This InstructionVisitor executes the instructions that it visits on a given local variable frame and stack.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Processor

        public Processor(Variables variables,
                 Stack stack,
                 ValueFactory valueFactory,
                 BranchUnit branchUnit,
                 InvocationUnit invocationUnit,
                 boolean alwaysCast)
        Creates a new processor that operates on the given environment.
        Parameters:
        variables - the local variable frame.
        stack - the local stack.
        valueFactory - the value factory that will create all values during the evaluation.
        branchUnit - the class that can affect the program counter.
        invocationUnit - the class that can access other program members.
        alwaysCast - a flag that specifies whether downcasts or casts of null values should always be performed.
